CENTOS 6 DISASTER RECOVERY USING REAR

--------------------------------------------------
1. Install ReaR
--------------------------------------------------

yum install rear


--------------------------------------------------
2. Configure ReaR
--------------------------------------------------

vi /etc/rear/local.conf

Add:

OUTPUT=ISO
BACKUP=NETFS
BACKUP_URL=nfs://192.168.0.46/nfsshare


--------------------------------------------------
3. Run Backup using Screen
--------------------------------------------------

Start screen session

screen -S backup

Run backup

rear -v -d mkbackup


--------------------------------------------------
4. Screen Session Commands
--------------------------------------------------

Check screen session

screen -ls

Reattach session

screen -r backup


--------------------------------------------------
5. Recovery on New Platform
--------------------------------------------------

This recovery process works on:

VMware
Nutanix
Physical Server
Any VM platform

Attach ReaR ISO to VM
Boot from ISO


--------------------------------------------------
6. Start Recovery
--------------------------------------------------

rear recover

During recovery select:

Do not map disks automatically

Then select:

ReaR shell


--------------------------------------------------
7. Create Disk Partition
--------------------------------------------------

parted /dev/sda

mklabel msdos
mkpart primary ext4 1MiB 1025MiB
set 1 boot on
mkpart primary ext4 1025MiB 100%
quit


Partition Layout:

/dev/sda1  -> /boot
/dev/sda2  -> LVM


--------------------------------------------------
8. Enter Recovered System
--------------------------------------------------

chroot /mnt/local


--------------------------------------------------
9. Install GRUB
--------------------------------------------------

grub

root (hd0,0)
setup (hd0)
quit

Install grub on disk

grub-install /dev/sda


--------------------------------------------------
10. Regenerate Initramfs
--------------------------------------------------

dracut -f


--------------------------------------------------
11. Verify Kernel Information
--------------------------------------------------

grubby --info=ALL


--------------------------------------------------
12. Remove Incorrect Root Parameter
--------------------------------------------------

grubby --update-kernel=ALL --remove-args="root=/dev/vg_centos-latest/lv_root"


--------------------------------------------------
13. Add Correct LVM Root Parameter
--------------------------------------------------

grubby --update-kernel=ALL --args="root=/dev/mapper/vg_centos--latest-lv_root"


--------------------------------------------------
14. Set Default Kernel
--------------------------------------------------

grubby --set-default /boot/vmlinuz-2.6.32-431.el6.x86_64


--------------------------------------------------
15. Verify GRUB Configuration
--------------------------------------------------

vi /boot/grub/grub.conf

Ensure correct root entry:

kernel /vmlinuz-2.6.32-431.el6.x86_64 ro root=/dev/mapper/vg_centos--latest-lv_root


--------------------------------------------------
16. Exit and Reboot
--------------------------------------------------

exit
reboot


--------------------------------------------------
RECOVERY COMPLETE
--------------------------------------------------

The system should now boot normally with the recovered disk.
